Help:Node.title: Command Usage: enter
Help:Node.Log:Description:
COMMAND USAGE: enter [exit]
EXAMPLE: enter purple door
Moves you out of a room by the specified exit. Exits may include doors, gates, holes, or any other means of egress. This command is useful for movement if an exit has not been assigned a direction, usually because there are multiple exits in the same direction.
